1.As this is a shell demonstartion, so UNIX based OS is a prerequisite.
2.You can download Ubuntu from https://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop
3.Copy the code and save it to the file.
4.Feel free to modify the code using any editor e.g. vi
5.Complie it using the command: gcc filename.
6.Execute the file using ./filename
7.Please keep in mind that:
    Arguments must be separated by whitespace.
    Commands must be on a single line.
    No quoting arguments or escaping whitespace.
    No piping or redirection.

